The paper is about a network intrusion detection system, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The use of bio-inspired optimization algorithms (BIOs) and quantum computing techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The optimization of the classification algorithm also implies a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the proposed system is designed to monitor and control network behavior, which could be seen as a system control problem (cs.SY).
